1. Base Projection Layer — Weighted averages from season stats, last 10 games, and last 5 games form the statistical baseline.

2. Adjustment Layer — Momentum, usage shifts, matchup difficulty, pace environment, fatigue, and astro transit modifiers refine the raw projection.

3. Simulation Layer — Monte Carlo simulations (100–10,000 iterations) generate probability distributions, median outcomes, and P10/P90 confidence bands.

4. Signal Layer — Pattern detection engines identify momentum streaks, over heaters, usage spikes, defense edges, and celestial alignments.

5. Confidence Layer — Edge size, simulation probability, and signal alignment combine into confidence tiers: Elite, Strong, Playable, and Neutral.','info','all',1,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-06 20:47:35.208145+00','2026-03-06 20:47:35.208145+00'),
('28563f9f-4cd2-4cbc-b600-16c99613c7f3','What Astra AI Does','what-astra-ai-does','Astra AI is the conversational intelligence layer.','Astra AI is the intelligence interface for CosmicEdge. It serves as the translator between raw data and actionable insight.

Astra can:
• Explain prop edges and why a line has value
• Break down model projections layer by layer
• Interpret active signals (momentum, usage, astro)
• Answer sports analytics questions with live data
• Run formulas from Celestial Engines in real time
• Explain simulation results and probability distributions
• Describe matchups, trends, and game scripts

When Astra receives a question, it: (1) detects the intent, (2) selects the relevant engine, (3) computes or retrieves values, and (4) generates an explanation.','info','all',2,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00'),
('96d8cdde-d424-4481-896e-fdba253f8552','Key Model Outputs','model-outputs','Key outputs: Edge Score, Confidence Tier, Simulation Probability, Signal Badges, Projection Breakdown, and Game Script analysis.','CosmicEdge produces several key outputs that users should monitor:

• Edge Score — Measures the gap between model projection and sportsbook line.
• Confidence Tier — Categorizes prop strength: Elite (70+), Strong (60–69), Playable (55–59), Neutral (below 55).
• Simulation Probability — The percentage chance a player clears the line based on Monte Carlo modeling.
• Signal Badges — Visual indicators like Momentum Rising, Over Heater, Usage Spike, Defense Edge, and astro signals.
• Projection Breakdown — Shows base projection plus each adjustment layer.
• Game Script — Predicts the likely game environment.','info','all',3,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00'),
('4c65f8ff-43a9-4422-8054-b3eaa1c9ca24','How CosmicEdge Differs','how-ce-differs','CosmicEdge evaluates lines through multi-layer engines — it explains WHY a line has value.','Most sportsbooks and prop browsers simply display lines and odds. CosmicEdge goes far beyond that:

• Sportsbooks show you WHAT the line is. CosmicEdge explains WHY it may be wrong.
• Basic prop browsers list markets. CosmicEdge evaluates each market through a multi-layer engine.
• Traditional tools rely on season averages. CosmicEdge uses recency-weighted projections, momentum detection, matchup modeling, pace normalization, and simulation.
• No other platform integrates celestial timing overlays as a contextual volatility signal.','info','all',4,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00'),
('fe0d23a2-dc33-4fe9-a175-7663c11e3102','Same Game Parlays','same-game-parlays','Explains how CosmicEdge evaluates same-game parlay combinations.','Same-game parlays are evaluated using pair relationships, same-player stat overlap, and adjusted joint probability instead of naive multiplication alone.','info','all',5,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-06 20:47:35.208145+00','2026-03-06 20:47:35.208145+00'),
('9f01cfdc-5e93-433d-b313-f9bdce1261e2','How Edge Score Works','how-edge-score-works','EdgeScore = Projection − Line. Converted to probability via logistic function.','Edge Score is the core value metric in CosmicEdge:

Formula: EdgeScore = Projection − Line

A positive edge means the model projects a higher stat than the sportsbook line, indicating value on the Over. A negative edge indicates value on the Under.

The raw edge is then converted to a probability-like score using logistic transformation.','methodology','all',2,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-06 20:47:35.208145+00','2026-03-06 20:47:35.208145+00'),
('9e6158e0-aaa8-4394-9445-8f6a5543943c','How Monte Carlo Works','how-monte-carlo-works','Repeated random sampling estimates the true probability of clearing a line.','Monte Carlo simulation is a statistical technique that uses repeated random sampling to estimate probability distributions.

How CosmicEdge uses it:
1. The adjusted projection provides a mean (mu) and standard deviation (sigma)
2. The engine generates N random samples from a normal distribution
3. Each sample represents one possible game outcome
4. The percentage of samples exceeding the line becomes the Over probability','methodology','all',3,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-06 20:47:35.208145+00','2026-03-06 20:47:35.208145+00'),
('6f2039cc-630a-4362-9ed2-9a533ef3c502','Data Collection Layer','data-collection','The data foundation: player stats, game logs, pace metrics, defensive rankings, sportsbook lines, live PBP, and celestial inputs.','CosmicEdge collects and maintains a comprehensive data ecosystem:

• Player Statistics — Game logs, season averages, rolling windows (L5, L10, L20), per-minute rates, and advanced metrics.
• Historical Game Logs — Complete box scores.
• Team Pace Metrics — Possessions per game, offensive/defensive rating, net rating.
• Defensive Rankings — Opponent stat-allowed rankings by category.
• Sportsbook Lines — Real-time prop lines, moneylines, spreads, and totals.
• Live Play-by-Play — Quarter-by-quarter scoring, live game state snapshots.
• Astro Inputs — Planetary positions, transit calculations, natal chart data.','methodology','all',1,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00'),
('4902aae2-8126-4c24-ba3e-cb7856702216','Projection Layer','projection-layer','Weighted averages with recency bias and pace normalization form the statistical baseline.','Base projections are generated using recency-weighted statistical modeling:

Base Projection Formula:
(Season Average × 0.50) + (Last 10 Average × 0.30) + (Last 5 Average × 0.20)

This formula balances long-term reliability with short-term trends.','methodology','all',2,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00'),
('20995baf-52b3-4170-ad86-bc99db5d4551','Adjustment Layer','adjustment-layer','Momentum, usage, matchup, pace, fatigue, game script, and astro layers refine the base projection.','Raw projections are refined through multiple adjustment engines:

• Momentum Engine — Compares recent averages to baseline.
• Usage Engine — Detects changes in offensive involvement.
• Matchup Engine — Evaluates opponent defensive effectiveness.
• Pace Engine — Measures possession inflation.
• Fatigue Engine — Adjusts for rest.
• Game Script Simulator — Predicts game environments.
• Astro Transit Engine — Applies celestial modifiers capped at ±3%.','methodology','all',3,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00'),
('e95d7a56-1972-46f7-8daf-a3551b8d9f5f','Simulation Layer','simulation-layer','Monte Carlo simulations generate probability distributions.','The simulation engine generates thousands of stat outcomes using Monte Carlo modeling:

Process:
1. Take the adjusted projection mean (mu) and standard deviation (sigma)
2. Run 100–10,000 random samples from Normal(mu, sigma)
3. Count how many samples exceed the sportsbook line

Outputs:
• Probability Over
• Probability Under
• Median Outcome
• P10 — 10th percentile
• P90 — 90th percentile','methodology','all',4,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00'),
('ba675aff-b3db-4ebf-b71e-75442a925861','Correlation Layer','correlation-layer','Detects statistical relationships between outcomes.','The correlation layer detects statistical relationships between outcomes:

• Game Environment Correlations — High-scoring games correlate with more assists and three-pointers.
• Player Stat Correlations — Some players show strong correlations between stats.
• 90-Day Correlation Flags — The Supermodel (v9) layer integrates 90-day rolling correlation data.','methodology','all',5,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00'),
('666cf81e-c857-40f4-9835-dfe358b5a4d7','Final Signal Generation','signal-generation','Edge Score, Edge Radar, Confidence Tiers, and Signal Badges combine into the final actionable output.','The final signal generation combines all layers into actionable intelligence:

Edge Score — Measures projection vs. line gap.
Edge Radar — Composite 0–100 score.
Confidence Tiers: Elite (70+), Strong (60–69), Playable (55–59), Neutral (below 55).
Signal Badges — Active indicators surfaced on props.','methodology','all',6,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00','2026-03-11 15:23:47.578767+00'),
('2a61c3b2-93ac-47e8-a011-5473d778d52e','Understanding Astro Overlays','understanding-astro-overlays','Celestial transits provide contextual volatility signals capped at ±3%.','The astro overlay is a contextual volatility layer — it does not replace statistical analysis:

How it works:
• Planetary transits are mapped to performance archetypes
• Player natal charts provide individual sensitivity to specific transits
• Game timing determines which celestial conditions are active during tip-off

Important: Astro adjustments are capped at ±3% of projection mean.','methodology','all',4,true,'[]','[]','2026-03-06 20:47:35.208145+00','2026-03-06 20:47:35.208145+00')
